This paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category as it deals with adversarial examples and defenses against them. It could also belong to the sub-categories of computer security (cs.CR) and computer vision (cs.CV) as these are related to the topic of adversarial attacks and defenses. Additionally, it could be classified under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) as these fields are closely related to machine learning.
